text: František Reich (born 31 October 1929) is a Slovak rower who competed for Czechoslovakia. He competed at the 1952 Summer Olympics in Helsinki in men's single sculls where he was eliminated in the semi-finals repêchage. ==References== Category:1929 births Category:Living people Category:Czechoslovak male rowers Category:Slovak male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of Czechoslovakia Category:Rowers at the 1952 Summer Olympics Category:Rowers at the 1956 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Žilina Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
